sentences: Timothy Patrick Kelly (January 13, 1963 – February 5, 1998) was an American guitarist for the band Slaughter.
After no real success with these bands, he was chosen as guitarist for the group Slaughter which was formed in the Fall of 1988.
On the first album of the band Stick It to Ya, he wrote and performed an instrumental piece called "Thinking of June" which he dedicated to his sister who died in 1982.
He was later sentenced to three years in prison.
